{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d70-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1974"},"text":"§ 1974.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Advisory Council on Servicemembers’ Group Life Insurance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d71-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" There is an Advisory Council on Servicemembers’ Group Life Insurance. The council consists of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d72-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary of the Treasury, who is the chairman of the council;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d73-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary of Defense;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d74-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary of Commerce;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d75-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary of Health and Human Services;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d76-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary of Homeland Security; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d77-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"Members of the council shall serve without additional compensation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d78-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1974/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The council shall meet at least once a year, or more often at the call of the Secretary of Veterans Affairs. The council shall review the operations of the Department under this subchapter and shall advise the Secretary on matters of policy relating to the Secretary’s activities under this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc3296d79-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/214/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–214, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/885"},"text":"79 Stat. 885","children":[],"tail":", § 774; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/291/s6"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–291, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/331"},"text":"84 Stat. 331","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/289/s10/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–289, § 10(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/172"},"text":"88 Stat. 172","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/295/s4/95/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–295, § 4(95)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1313"},"text":"96 Stat. 1313","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/576/tVII/s701/41"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–576, title VII, § 701(41)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3294"},"text":"100 Stat. 3294","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/54/s14/b/18"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–54, § 14(b)(18)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-06-13"},"text":"June 13, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/284"},"text":"105 Stat. 284","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 1974, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/406"},"text":"105 Stat. 406","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/275/tIV/s405/b/1/G"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–275, title IV, § 405(b)(1)(G)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3339"},"text":"110 Stat. 3339","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/183/tVII/s708/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–183, title VII, § 708(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-12-16"},"text":"Dec. 16, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/2673"},"text":"117 Stat. 2673","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc3296d7a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc3296d7b-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc3296d7c-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (a)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/183"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–183","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Secretary of Homeland Security” for “Secretary of Transportation”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/275/s405/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–275, § 405(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Servicemembers’ Group” for “Servicemen’s Group” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/275/s405/b/1/G"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–275, § 405(b)(1)(G)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Servicemembers’ Group” for “Servicemen’s Group” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s774"},"text":"section 774 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/54"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–54","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section read as follows: “There is hereby established an Advisory Council on Servicemen’s Group Life Insurance consisting of the Secretary of the Treasury as Chairman, the Secretary of Defense, the Secretary of Commerce, the Secretary of Health and Human Services, the Secretary of Transportation, and the Director of the Office of Management and Budget each of whom shall serve without additional compensation. The Council shall meet once a year, or oftener at the call of the Administrator, and shall review the operations under this subchapter and advise the Administrator on matters of policy relating to the Administrator activities thereunder.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/576"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–576","children":[],"tail":" substituted “the Administrator” for “his” before “activities”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–295","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Health and Human Services” for “Health, Education, and Welfare”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1974—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/289"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–289","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Office of Management and Budget” for “Bureau of the Budget”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1970—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/291"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–291","children":[],"tail":" added the Secretary of Transportation to the membership of the Advisory Council on Servicemen’s Group Life Insurance."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc3296d7d-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idc3296d7e-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1970 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/291"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–291","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1970","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/291/s14/a"},"text":"section 14(a) of Pub. L. 91–291","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1317"},"text":"section 1317 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idc3296d7f-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of Advisory Councils","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Advisory councils in existence on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 1973","children":[],"tail":", to terminate not later than the expiration of the 2-year period following "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 1973","children":[],"tail":", unless, in the case of a council established by the President or an officer of the Federal Government, such council is renewed by appropriate action prior to the expiration of such 2-year period, or in the case of a council established by the Congress, its duration is otherwise provided by law. See 